Rating: 3
I just made this for the second time and this is yummy. I mixed the dressing and let it sit in the fridge for a while before tossing it with the pasta which I'd recommend because I found the lemon flavor too strong. I used "light" mayo and light sour cream and after adjusting the amounts, I probably used 3/4 cup each to tone down the lemon. Only used 3 Tbsp olive oil. I added red and orange bell pepper for color and crunch and also added scallops. I love cold salads for dinner on hot summer evenings, and this is a good one. Just be sure to taste/adjust the dressing before you toss and do save the pasta water in case you want to thin it down a bit.

